# pagehub-benchmarks — environment.  Copy to .env (gitignored) and edit.

# --- harness: Claude Code ---------------------------------------------------
# Benchmark runs use the `claude` CLI's existing logged-in auth (a Claude
# subscription — flat-rate, not metered API billing). The adapter explicitly
# UNSETS ANTHROPIC_API_KEY in the subprocess so a stray key can't divert the
# run onto API billing — don't set one here. If `claude -p` says "not logged
# in", run `claude login`. (cost_usd in results is a *computed* figure:
# tokens x pricing.yaml = "what this would cost at API rates".)

# Max seconds for one `claude` invocation (one attempt). Default 3600.
# CLAUDE_BUILD_TIMEOUT_SECONDS=3600

# --- grader: pagehub-evals --------------------------------------------------
# Where the pagehub-evals repo is checked out (the grader resolves a
# benchmark's grader.fixture_bundle path relative to this). Default:
# ~/github/pagehub-io/pagehub-evals
# PAGEHUB_EVALS_REPO=~/github/pagehub-io/pagehub-evals

# Operator bearer token for pagehub-evals (fixture import + resource listing
# are operator-only). If unset, a dev HS256 token is minted from the values
# below — only works against a dev pagehub-evals (docker-compose defaults).
# PAGEHUB_EVALS_TOKEN=eyJ...
# PAGEHUB_EVALS_JWT_SIGNING_KEY=dev-kid:local-dev-jwt-signing-key-DO-NOT-USE-IN-PROD
# PAGEHUB_EVALS_JWT_ISSUER=http://localhost:8080
# PAGEHUB_EVALS_OPERATOR_EMAIL=support@pagehub.io
